'''Tory Belleci''', also credited as '''Salvatore Belleci''', (b. [[October 30]], [[1970]] in [[Wikipedia:Monterey, California|Monterey, California]]) worked for [[Industrial Light & Magic]] as a model builder, sculptor, and painter. During his eight years of working for ILM, he contributed to [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''The Phantom Menace'']] and [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']]. He also appeared in ''[[R2-D2: Beneath the Dome]]'' as Cop #1, or Starsky. His other notable works include, but are not limited to, ''Scooby-Doo'', ''Matrix'' and ''Van Helsing''.

He appeared for several years on the ''MythBusters'' show on the Discovery Channel, prior to a restructuring of the program. He is also an Honorary Member of the [[501st Legion (fan organization)|501st Legion]].

